summary: In a surprising move, the Chicago Cubs have traded outfielder Cody Bellinger to the New York Yankees in exchange for right-handed pitcher Cody Poteet. In return, the Cubs acquire Poteet, a 27-year-old reliever who has been a reliable option for the Yankees. Poteet is known for his control and ability to induce ground balls, making him a valuable addition to the Cubs' bullpen. The trade marks the latest shake-up in the MLB landscape, as teams continue to prepare for the upcoming season.

name: Vanuatu
summary: A devastating magnitude 7.3 earthquake has caused widespread damage in the Pacific island nation of Vanuatu. The quake has resulted in multiple deaths, with reports ranging from six to 14 fatalities. Buildings have collapsed, including the U.S. embassy, leaving people trapped in the rubble. Search and rescue operations are underway, but communication issues are hindering efforts to assess the full extent of the damage. Cyclone Chido, which passed near Vanuatu before the earthquake, has exacerbated the situation, complicating relief efforts in the wake of the natural disaster.

summary: In a setback for progressive Democrats, Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez (AOC) lost her bid to become the top Democrat on the House Oversight Committee.
